        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 12:19PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1218 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
St. Marys, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elida, Yoder, Conant, Westminster, Spencerville, Spencerville In
Allen County, Hume, Harrod, Slabtown, Fort Shawnee, Bluffton,
Rousculp, Beaverdam, Cairo, Lima, Rockport, and Kemp.

This includes Interstate 75 between mile markers 119 and 141.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
